Trim the @carrot{1}(halved lengthways and sliced into 1/2cm thick pieces), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Slice widthways into pieces about 1/2cm thick.

Halve and peel the @onion{1}(halved and chopped into 2cm chunks).

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g}, carrot and onion.

Fry until the mince has browned and the veg has softened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

While the beef and veg cook, boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{80%g}(trimmed and cut into thirds), then cut into thirds.

Pour the boiled water from the kettle into a medium #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring to a boil. Add the green beans and @egg noodle nests{125%g} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir the @ginger puree{15%g} into the pan and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @hoisin sauce{30%g}, @ketjap manis{50%g}, @soy sauce{25%ml} and @water for the sauce{100%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir the cooked noodles and beans into the sauce.

Taste and season with @salt and @pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Share the noodles, beef and veg between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the peanuts to finish. Enjoy!

> Step 2 MOD: If you've chosen beef mince instead of pork, cook the recipe in the same way.